  "text": "To the best of our knowledge, this is the first study that correlates community macrolide resistance levels with treatment outcomes for CAP. Community-level resistance and treatment outcomes for suppurative acute otitis media, acute sinusitis and acute exacerbation of chronic bronchitis, however, have been evaluated. This study, conducted by Furuno et al., [CITATION_1] did not find an association between resistance level and outcomes, with the exception of a positive correlation between non-susceptibility to erythromycin isolates and macrolide treatment resolution (P ¼ 0.04).",
